  <h2>Introduction</h2>
  <p>ITIL (the IT Infrastructure Library) is the most widely accepted approach 
        to IT service management in the world, ITIL provides a comprehensive and 
        consistent set of best practices for IT service management, promoting 
        a quality approach to achieving business effectiveness and efficiency 
        in the use of information systems.</p>
  <p>ITIL is based on the collective experience of commercial and governmental 
        practitioners worldwide. This has been distilled into one reliable, coherent 
        approach, which is fast becoming a de facto standard used by some of the 
        world's leading businesses.</p>
  
<p>For more detailed information on how to use this ITIL Web 
        CD see the Help page. Should you require technical support on this CD 
        contact TSO by telephone or email, details of which 
        are contained in the <a href="help.htm">Help Page</a>.</p>
  
<p>TSO would welcome your views on our products, so that 
        we can continually improve them. If you would like to comment on this 
        new electronic ITIL  publication, please take a moment 
        to fill in our <a href="feedback.htm">Feedback Form</a> and 
        express your opinions. Please <a href="privacy.htm">click here</a> to 
        read TSO's Privacy Policy.</p>
